&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7189&quot; title=&quot;Allow DIH to extract content from embedded documents via Tika&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7189&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7189&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Allow DIH to extract content from embedded documents via Tika&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14352368" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 00:22:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1665100 from shalin@apache.org in branch &apos;dev/branches/branch_5x&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1665100&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1665100&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7189&quot; title=&quot;Allow DIH to extract content from embedded documents via Tika&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7189&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7189&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Allow DIH to extract content from embedded documents via Tika&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14352371" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 00:25:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Tim!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14352802" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 11:01:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shalin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;shalin&quot;&gt;shalin&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On a related note, as of Tika 1.7, it&apos;s easy to handle embedded documents as individual documents and maintain the embedded documents&apos; metadata via the RecursiveParserWrapper.  Until Tika 1.7, the off-the-shelf handlers concatenated the content of embedded documents but didn&apos;t maintain the embedded documents&apos; metadata.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you think there would be interest in adding a parameter to DIH to create individual child documents for embedded documents and maintain their metadata?  Separate issue, of course.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14352807" author="shalinmangar" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 11:05:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can imagine uses for it but personally I don&apos;t use much of either tika or DIH so I&apos;ll defer to your judgement. I&apos;m happy to shepherd any patches though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14352813" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 11:09:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it.  If anyone has an interest, I&apos;ll draft a patch, but otherwise this should do for now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you, again!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14353039" author="arafalov" created="Mon, 9 Mar 2015 14:34:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think if the new functionality allows to look inside zips for example, a lot of people would be interested. And it should be exposed through inner entity mechanism, so people could start with a list of file names for zips, then expand the zips, then process individual files, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But yes, it should be a separate issue. And I would definitely create it so the people are even aware of this new functionality.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14356135" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2015 02:55:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7229&quot; title=&quot;Allow DIH to handle attachments as separate documents&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7229&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7229&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Will need help and input on what the default behavior should be on the Solr side.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14495252" author="thelabdude" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2015 00:30:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close after 5.1 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16871743" author="nicolas.larcipretti" created="Mon, 24 Jun 2019 19:57:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this solution works with PDF&apos;s as well? I was able to extract text from images (png) and images within docx, but could not with images within PDF&apos;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

